comments.body: [~aauld] Please describe how the fade in/fade out should look between each button.

[~homer]

Let's use Zillow's Home Page as an example: [https://www.zillow.com/]

 

Rollover Design: https://zpl.io/bPrmZMk
Images not ready - product manager will need to supply images

[~homer] images are uploaded in all sizes for each tab.  When we implement the Desarrollos tab, then we wil use the Comprar image for Desarrollos (for now).

Note that the height of the mobile image has increased to 400px, this is to make room for the addition of the SEO tag below the intentions menu and also the New Dev banner for when we implement it.

Hi, the adpos for each tab will be from left to right:

*Desktop*

SK_1_HP_D

SK_2_HP_D

SK_3_HP_D

SK_4_HP_D

*Mobile*

SK_1_HP_M

SK_2_HP_M

SK_3_HP_M

SK_4_HP_M

Please let me know if you have some questions,
Need to see the result (basically performance of ad) in VM before deciding whether to release it.

items.fromString: Please follow design on the dropdown menu, so they aren't the default ones used by browser. Applicable to desktop only.
items.toString:
As the intention menu changes from "buy" "rent" "share" two things will happen:

1) Transition graphics 
2) The search button text changes from "Buscar" to something else. It'll stay as "buscar" for mobile, but changes on desktop.
